Files:
- plugins/stripe/src/stripe-api.ts (add signal to init, fix catch block)

Context:
Current code (lines 72-90):
  const init: RequestInit = {
    method,
    headers,
    credentials: 'include',
    // NO signal here!
  };
  ...
  try {
    response = await fetch(url, init);
  } catch (error: unknown) {
    if (error instanceof DOMException && error.name === 'AbortError') { // DEAD — no signal
      throw ToolError.timeout('Request timed out.');
    }
    throw ToolError.internal(...);
  }

Changes:
1. Add `signal: AbortSignal.timeout(30_000)` to the init object
2. Change the catch block to check `error.name === 'TimeoutError'` (not 'AbortError') — AbortSignal.timeout() fires TimeoutError, not AbortError

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the auth header construction or body encoding logic
- The 30_000ms timeout must match the platform convention (all other plugins use 30s)
- Do NOT use fetchFromPage here — this API requires a custom Authorization header (Bearer session_api_key) that is different from the page's session cookies, so raw fetch() is appropriate
